commitResults.messageBody:
Added echo function to Psyduck bot.
Use command "Bye" to exit the bot.

Added a list function for Psyduck.
Any text other than the special commands will add the task to a list.
Added exit as an option to exit the program.
Unfinished debugging to do with marking and unmarking tasks.

commitResults.messageTitle: Reworked Psyduck.java to process inputs better
commitResults.messageBody: TodoList.java: added ability to get task description

commitResults.messageTitle: Renamed ToDoList class to ToDo class
commitResults.messageBody:
Refactor code to fit inheritance for the ToDo class from the Task class

Currently there are errors with method calls for markDone(), unmarkDone() and Todo()

commitResults.messageTitle: Task classes: Changed properties of Task class to accommodate child classes
commitResults.messageBody:
ToDo class now works as a child of the Task class

Prior errors are now fixed

Deadline class inherits from Task class with a deadline property

Adjust Psyduck main() method to accommodate the new Deadline class

Psyduck can now add tasks that are of Deadline type

Contains the Event class which inherits from the Task class.

Add addEvent() method to Psyduck class

To accommodate the new task type
Refactor code to meet code quality standards

commitResults.messageTitle: Refactor Psyduck class by auto indenting
Reorganise code to fit command related methods into Command.java
commitResults.messageBody:
Most of the code that do not have to deal with managing the list of
task is reorganised into a Command class

commitResults.messageTitle: Add NullPointerException catch for marking and unmarking tasks
commitResults.messageBody:
This will catch errors to prevent users from accessing unintialised
Task.

Add a line to remind users how many tasks are in the list

commitResults.messageTitle: Add NumberFormatException for marking/unmarking of tasks
commitResults.messageBody:
This exception will catch erroneous user inputs who input a string
after the command "mark". Also minor changes to the formatting for
printing of total number of tasks.

Now correctly outputs 'task' or 'tasks' depending on number of
tasks in the list.
